Reproductive tract variable in length, extending part-way along dorsal pharyngeal gland or to nerve ring; outstretched or singly reflexed; oviduct with oocytes not in rows; uterus containing no eggs or occasionally one egg (in 2 of
24 specimens
); vulva with lips protruding or flat, or a depressed slit. With SEM, anterior lip of vulva overlap of posterior lip visible at lateral edges (suggesting that posterior lip is depressed for egg deposition). Tail tapering, often arcuate; length 1.6–2.5 times anal body diameter, tip rounded.
